dict.string: Add current Firefox page to Safari's reading list
on alfred_script(q) tell application "Firefox" set pageUrl to get URL of active tab of first window end tell tell application "Safari" to add reading list item pageUrl end alfred_script

if [ $# -eq 0 ]; then bullet="* " else bullet=$1 fi
pbpaste | nl -s "$bullet " | cut -c7- | pbcopy
Prepend a bullet character to the text in the pasteboard

require 'csv' query = ARGV[0]
if query col_sep = query else col_sep = "\t" end
clipboard = `pbpaste` rows = CSV.parse(clipboard, col_sep: col_sep) column_widths = [] markdown_rows = [] separators = "" rows.each { |row| row.each_with_index { |cell, x|
if !cell.nil? if column_widths[x] column_widths[x] = cell.length if cell.length > column_widths[x] else column_widths[x] = cell.length end end
} } rows.each { |row| markdown = "| " row.each_with_index { |cell, index| cell = "" if cell.nil? padding = " " * (column_widths[index] - cell.length + 1) markdown += cell + padding + "| " } markdown_rows << markdown.strip } column_widths.each { |width| separators << "|" + ("-" * (width + 2)) } separators += "|" markdown_rows.insert(1,separators) print markdown_rows.join("\n")
Assumes tab separated but specify , for comma separated
Convert a TSV table into Markdown

pbdata = `pbpaste` pattern = "\n" replacement = '\n' result = pbdata.gsub(pattern, replacement) print result
pbdata = `pbpaste` pattern = '{query}' replacement = '' result = pbdata.delete(pattern) print result
Replace pattern in pasteboard text with space
pbdata = `pbpaste` result = "" pbdata.each_line do |line| result += line[2..-1] end print result
pbdata = `pbpaste` results = "" pbdata.each_line do |line| results += line.strip + "\n" end print results.chomp
